The zChaff license forbids redistribution, so it must be downloaded separately.

To use zChaff in DE:
  1) Download https://www.princeton.edu/~chaff/zchaff/zchaff.2004.5.13.tar.gz
  2) Uncompress it and place the sources in the ./zchaff/ directory of DE
     (i.e., ./zchaff/zchaff_base.cpp should exist).
  3) Uncomment the ZCHAFF=1 line in DE's Makefile.
  4) make DE in the usual way.

You may need to add
#include <stdlib.h>
to zchaff/zchaff_base.cpp and zchaff/zchaff_dbase.cpp .
